  "text": "The Grafana alerting evaluation scheduler is implemented in the ngalert package and consists of several interconnected components:\n\n## Scheduler Tick Implementation\nThe scheduler tick is initiated in `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go`. The `schedulePeriodic()` method (line 248) implements the main scheduler loop that receives ticks from a ticker and processes them. For each tick, it calls `processTick()` (line 278) which determines which alert rules are ready for evaluation and schedules them.\n\nThe actual ticker that emits ticks at regular intervals is in `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/ticker/ticker.go`. The `T.run()` method (line 55) implements the ticker that emits ticks on interval marks at predictable times.\n\n## Evaluation Cycle Overrun Detection and Logging\nThe warning message \"Tick dropped because alert rule evaluation is too slow\" is logged in `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go` in the `runJobFn()` method (lines 441-445). This method sends evaluation signals to alert rule routines and checks if any ticks were dropped.\n\nThe actual timeout detection happens in `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/alert_rule.go` in the `Eval()` method (line 206). This method implements a non-blocking check of the evaluation channel. If a new evaluation arrives while the previous one is still in progress (still pending in the channel), the previous evaluation is captured as `droppedMsg` and returned to the caller. This indicates that the evaluation cycle has overrun its time budget.\n\nThe alert rule evaluation loop is in the `Run()` method (line 251), which processes evaluation signals. The actual evaluation execution happens in the `evaluate()` method (line 400).\n\n## Evaluation Timeout Application\nThe evaluation timeout budget is applied in `pkg/services/ngalert/eval/eval.go` in the `EvaluateRaw()` method (lines 74-77). The `EvaluationTimeout` configuration is used to create a timeout context with `context.WithTimeout()`, which enforces a deadline for the evaluation execution.\n\nThe flow is: `schedulePeriodic()` → `processTick()` → `runJobFn()` which calls `alertRule.Eval()` → `alertRule.Run()` processes evaluations → `alertRule.evaluate()` executes evaluation → `EvaluateRaw()` applies timeout. When `alertRule.Eval()` detects a dropped tick (overrun evaluation), the warning is logged in `runJobFn()`."
}

